# Testing Conventions

## Framework
- Use **Vitest** — NOT Jest, Mocha, or Jasmine
- Test runner config: `vitest.config.mts` at root
- Run tests: `yarn test` (all) or `yarn test packages/excalidraw` (specific)

## Test Structure (AAA Pattern)
```typescript
describe("ComponentName", () => {
  it("should do specific thing", () => {
    // Arrange — set up test data
    const element = createTestElement();

    // Act — perform the action
    const result = processElement(element);

    // Assert — verify the outcome
    expect(result.type).toBe("rectangle");
  });
});
```

## File Organization
- Colocate tests with source: `Component.tsx` → `Component.test.tsx`
- Integration tests in `excalidraw-app/tests/`
- Use existing test helpers from `packages/excalidraw/tests/helpers/`

## Coverage Thresholds
- Lines: 60%
- Branches: 70%
- Functions: 63%
- Statements: 60%

## Best Practices
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- Use `renderScene` helpers for canvas-related tests
- DO NOT mock `actionManager` — use the real one with test state
- Use `createTestElement()` helpers for element fixtures
- Snapshot tests: regenerate with `yarn test -u`, never edit manually

## How to verify
- All new tests use `describe/it` from Vitest (not Jest globals)
- Tests follow AAA pattern (Arrange/Act/Assert sections)
- No `jest.` API calls in new test files
- Coverage doesn't drop below thresholds after changes
